I'm finished with this place. I tried them when they first opened, and the food and service were good. I started with House Special Fried Rice, and it was good. I followed up with a few other familiar dishes for comparison, and found hem disappointing and strange. Like someone was not used to cooking these foods. So I stuck with the HFR. About a year ago I decided to compare them to few other Chinese restaurants in the area, and I found their food to be fresh, tasty and a fair value. Then I began having problems with my orders. Missing items and being charged for a free item to start, but then, much more importantly, the quality, method of preparation and consistency from one order to the next was more than I could accept. Like the food was coming from a different restaurant. I've had variances in restaurants before, but never like this. I've ordered my last meal from this place.

I'm beyond pissed!!!! I order frm this place alll the time and this is the first time they f**ked up, today was not the day! They put vegetables in my rice when I specifically said NO VEGETABLES! Its a lunch special so u get a soda with it so the delivery man brings me my food, it was $6.50 btw I gave a $10 bill so he should've given me $3.50 back but decided to give me only $3 but I was nice and still gave him a $2 tip since it's cold out, he leaves and that's when I notice my food was wrong and there wasn't even a soda in the bag, the guy left already so i called the restaurant to complain and the lady had the audacity to ask me why don't I just eat the vegetables!?!? R u f**king kidding me lady! First of all I should've been refunded cause that's what good customer service is, and then I had to wait for them to cook it and deliver again and when the delivery man gets here its a different guy, he looks at me as if hes waiting for me to tip him again!!!!!!! by the time I'm eating my lunch break is almost done!! F**king morons!!!! I have no sympathy or patience for pple who f**k up the worlds simplest food order! If I could give u negative stars I would!!!!

I ordered been lo me in with no vegetables for take out. I got home and they were the driest noodles I've ever had. The beef was tough and chewy, and there wasnt very much of it. sometimes I would either completely avoid the beef or give up half way through- it was just too tough.  However, the noodles weren't just dry as a bone but also bland and tasteless. I ended up pouring a bunch of olive oil and a bit of hot sauce to season it a bit and it became edible but their prices are just too high for the worst chinese food I've ever had.
